  "response": "Virat Kohli's remarkable energy and fitness levels can be attributed to several key factors:\n\n1. **Strict Fitness Regime**: Kohli follows a disciplined and rigorous fitness routine that includes strength training, cardio, and flexibility exercises. His commitment to fitness is well-known, and he often works with professional trainers to maintain peak physical condition.\n\n2. **Diet and Nutrition**: Kohli has adopted a clean and healthy diet, which includes a balanced intake of proteins, carbohydrates, and healthy fats. He is known to avoid junk food, alcohol, and sugary drinks, focusing instead on nutrient-rich foods that enhance his energy levels and recovery.\n\n3. **Mental Toughness**: Kohli's mental resilience and focus play a significant role in his energetic performances. He practices mindfulness and meditation to stay mentally sharp and maintain a positive mindset.\n\n4. **Rest and Recovery**: Adequate rest and recovery are crucial for maintaining energy levels. Kohli ensures he gets sufficient sleep and incorporates recovery techniques such as ice baths, massages, and stretching into his routine.\n\n5. **Passion and Motivation**: Kohli's passion for cricket and his desire to continually improve and perform at the highest level drive his energy and dedication. His love for the game and commitment to excellence are evident in his performances.\n\n6. **Professional Support**: Kohli has access to a team of professionals, including nutritionists, physiotherapists, and sports psychologists, who help him optimize his physical and mental well-being.\n\n7. **Genetics**: While hard work and discipline are paramount, genetics also play a role in an individual's energy levels and athletic performance. Kohli may naturally possess a high level of stamina and endurance.\n\nBy combining these elements, Virat Kohli maintains his exceptional energy and fitness, allowing him to perform consistently at the highest levels of international cricket.",
